entries.name: GatewayTransactionFilterer
entries.description: A contract implementing the ITransactionFilterer interface, filtering with a configurable whitelist of sender addresses and a blacklist of target contract addresses. Chain migration transactions are generally whitelisted. The filter lists are managed by the owner (eth:0xFe94B8AEB7950a26C276EA615a6d3C7289Fd2ac3).

receivedPermissions.description: define addresses that can send transactions from L1 to L2 (e.g. for deposits, withdrawals, queued transactions). This is enforced in the Mailbox Facet.

blacklistedContracts.description: Addresses that are blacklisted as target contracts for requestL2Transaction() calls.

whitelistedSenders.description: Addresses that are whitelisted as senders for requestL2Transaction() calls.

entries.name: Gateway
entries.description: The main contract defining the Gateway settlement layer. Operator actions like commiting blocks, providing ZK proofs and executing batches ultimately target this contract which then processes transactions. During batch execution it processes L1 --> L2 and L2 --> L1 transactions. Bridging transactions that target L2s settling on the Gateway are routed through this contract and proofs are aggregated on L1. Data availability for rollups on the Gateway is provided by the Gateway operators sending the data together with Gateway data.. isPermanentRollup was set to true in this contract which prevents changing the DA mode to Validium in the future.

isPermanentRollup.description: true means that the DA mode cannot be changed to Validium in the future. compliant DAValidator pairs for the permanent rollup mode are defined/enforced by the RollupDAManager contract.

entries.name: ValidatorTimelock
entries.description: Intermediary contract between the *Validators* and the central diamond contract that delays block execution (ie withdrawals and other L2 --> L1 messages) by 3h.

receivedPermissions.description: commit, prove, execute, revert batches directly in the main Diamond contract. This role is typically held by a proxying ValidatorTimelock.
